WEBVTT

00:07.107 --> 00:09.041
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:09.043 --> 00:10.676
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:10.678 --> 00:12.578
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:12.580 --> 00:14.146
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles</i>

00:14.148 --> 00:15.914
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:15.916 --> 00:18.684
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:18.686 --> 00:20.085
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house</i>

00:20.087 --> 00:21.320
<i>♪ In the Loud house</i>

00:21.322 --> 00:23.155
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:23.157 --> 00:24.490
<i>♪ Is how we show our love</i>

00:24.492 --> 00:26.458
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:26.460 --> 00:27.993
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls</i>

00:27.995 --> 00:29.595
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:29.597 --> 00:33.032
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud</i>

00:33.034 --> 00:34.333
<i>♪ Loud house</i>

00:34.335 --> 00:35.934
- Poo-poo.

00:36.136 --> 00:40.105
<i>[peppy music]</i>

00:40.107 --> 00:46.845
<i>♪</i>

00:46.847 --> 00:49.882
<i>[curious music]</i>
<i>- Hmm.</i>

00:49.884 --> 00:52.251
These totes bring out
your nose.

00:52.253 --> 00:54.253
Here, don't want you
getting cold.

00:54.255 --> 00:56.588
- Hey, Leni.
- Who told you my name?

00:56.590 --> 00:59.992
Oh, I'm wearing a nametag.

00:59.994 --> 01:00.959
- Shift's over.

01:00.961 --> 01:01.927
Let's go get pretzels.

01:01.929 --> 01:05.330
- Oh, it's you guys.
- Nice window dressing.

01:05.331 --> 01:07.332
You made the 'kins
look like friends.

01:07.334 --> 01:09.968
- Thanks.
I modeled them after us.

01:09.970 --> 01:12.404
<i>[ding]</i>

01:12.406 --> 01:13.639
[all munching]

01:13.641 --> 01:15.407
That's him, right?
Burger guy?

01:15.409 --> 01:17.376
- Yeah.
I'm so nervous about tonight.

01:17.378 --> 01:20.012
I haven't been on a date
since things fizzled

01:20.014 --> 01:21.513
with smoothie guy.

01:21.515 --> 01:23.048
<i>[mournful music]</i>

01:23.050 --> 01:25.517
- We'll come over after work
and help you get ready.

01:25.519 --> 01:28.320
Right, Miguel?
- Oh, I am yours, girl.

01:28.322 --> 01:31.323
- [gasps]
Hey, Leni.

01:31.325 --> 01:32.624
[girls squeal]

01:32.626 --> 01:35.360
[all kissing]

01:35.362 --> 01:36.528
- What a fun surprise.

01:36.530 --> 01:38.964
These are my two best friends
at school,

01:38.966 --> 01:40.466
Jackie and Mandee,
and these are

01:40.468 --> 01:43.068
my two best friends at work,
Miguel and Fiona.

01:43.070 --> 01:44.103
girls: Hey.
- Oh, hi.

01:44.105 --> 01:46.605
- Leni, we bought
so many cute shoes.

01:46.607 --> 01:49.174
- With money to spare
for the pop-up sale

01:49.176 --> 01:50.442
this weekend.
- Yes!

01:50.444 --> 01:51.643
Pop-up sale!
[screams]

01:51.645 --> 01:54.012
- Sounds like you guys
have a lot to talk about.

01:54.014 --> 01:55.614
I should mosey.
- Yeah, me, too.

01:55.616 --> 01:57.483
But we'll see you tonight,
Leni.

01:57.485 --> 01:59.318
- See you at 7:00!

01:59.320 --> 02:01.253
<i>[mournful music]</i>

02:01.255 --> 02:04.223
- Wait, you're hanging out
with those guys tonight?

02:04.225 --> 02:04.990
- Well, yeah.

02:04.992 --> 02:06.125
Is that bad?
- It's fine.

02:06.127 --> 02:08.259
I mean, I can't remember
the last time we spent

02:08.262 --> 02:11.029
a Friday night together,
but it's fine.

02:11.031 --> 02:12.164
- No, no, it's not fine.

02:12.166 --> 02:14.633
If I'm not making enough time
for you guys,

02:14.635 --> 02:15.567
I need to fix that.

02:15.569 --> 02:18.504
I'll come over after I'm done
at Fiona's house, okay?

02:18.506 --> 02:21.106
- Sounds good.
- See you laters.

02:21.108 --> 02:22.141
<i>[mellow music]</i>

02:22.143 --> 02:23.208
<i>- I hate first dates.</i>

02:23.210 --> 02:24.943
What--what if we have nothing
to talk about?

02:24.945 --> 02:27.246
- Don't worry,
you can use this list

02:27.248 --> 02:30.282
of 25 first-date questions
I found.

02:30.284 --> 02:31.250
[phone vibrating]

02:31.252 --> 02:33.619
Oh, what time are you leaving
for your date, Fiona?

02:33.621 --> 02:35.154
I should let Jackie
and Mandee know

02:35.156 --> 02:37.689
when to expect me.
- Wait, you double-booked us?

02:37.691 --> 02:39.625
- No, I just made
two separate plans

02:39.627 --> 02:41.660
for the same night.
- I mean, that's legit

02:41.662 --> 02:43.562
what a double-book is,
but it's fine.

02:43.564 --> 02:46.165
- Yeah, go be with
your school friends.

02:46.167 --> 02:47.399
We have this covered.

02:47.401 --> 02:49.968
- But I'll see you guys
at the pop-up sale

02:49.970 --> 02:50.669
this weekend?

02:50.671 --> 02:52.971
- I mean, sure.
- Yeah, I guess.

02:52.973 --> 02:53.672
<i>♪</i>

02:53.674 --> 02:55.474
- Hey, guys!
I'm so glad we can hang out.

02:55.476 --> 02:58.610
Tell me what's new with you.
- Oh, my gosh, so much.

02:58.612 --> 03:02.147
I'm not sure I want to be
a veterinarian anymore.

03:02.149 --> 03:04.616
- I'm thinking about
getting bangs.

03:04.618 --> 03:06.185
[phone vibrating]

03:06.187 --> 03:08.153
- Wow, that is big.

03:08.155 --> 03:10.589
Speaking of bangs,
I should go check mine.

03:10.591 --> 03:12.524
Make sure they're not too flat.

03:12.526 --> 03:13.625
BRB.

03:13.627 --> 03:14.526
<i>[sneaky music]</i>

03:14.528 --> 03:16.728
Sorry, really gotta
get in there.

03:16.730 --> 03:20.299
Fiona, what's the matter?
- Sorry to bother you guys,

03:20.301 --> 03:21.099
but I need help.

03:21.101 --> 03:22.734
We already got through
those 25 questions.

03:22.736 --> 03:24.570
His answer to every one was...

03:24.572 --> 03:25.571
[deep voice]
I guess.

03:25.573 --> 03:28.006
- There have to be other things
you can talk about.

03:28.008 --> 03:30.275
I know, tell him about the time

03:30.277 --> 03:31.476
you went to Canada.

03:31.478 --> 03:33.679
Guys love adventure!

03:33.681 --> 03:34.546
- Are you okay?

03:34.548 --> 03:36.181
I thought I heard you
talking to someone.

03:36.183 --> 03:39.451
- Oh, yeah, I was just
talking to...

03:39.453 --> 03:40.519
myself.

03:40.521 --> 03:41.587
It helps me pee.

03:41.589 --> 03:42.421
[phone vibrating]

03:42.423 --> 03:44.523
Uh, but it didn't work.
I should go again.

03:44.525 --> 03:46.692
This time I'll try singing.

03:49.495 --> 03:50.796
- [panting, groans]

03:50.798 --> 03:53.065
- ♪ Row-row-row your boat

03:53.067 --> 03:54.800
♪ Gently down the stream

03:54.802 --> 03:55.634
[phone vibrating]

03:55.636 --> 03:58.170
- Leni, guess who's seated
at the table next to mine?

03:58.172 --> 03:58.870
Smoothie guy!

03:58.872 --> 04:01.540
And he looks so cute
and sensitive.

04:01.542 --> 04:04.409
- Move to another table
immediately.

04:04.411 --> 04:05.310
- Focus on burger guy.

04:05.312 --> 04:06.778
It didn't work
with smoothie guy, remember?

04:06.780 --> 04:08.247
Don't get sucked back
into that blender.

04:08.249 --> 04:11.516
- Thanks, guys.
- ♪ Life is but a dream

04:11.518 --> 04:14.419
[toilet flushes]

04:14.421 --> 04:15.254
[phone vibrating]

04:15.256 --> 04:16.688
You know what we need?
Snacks!

04:16.690 --> 04:19.658
Don't get up,
your nails are wet.

04:19.660 --> 04:21.560
[gasps]
Smoothie guy sent you

04:21.562 --> 04:23.562
some chili fries,
and now burger guy

04:23.564 --> 04:27.132
is going over there
to confront him?

04:27.134 --> 04:28.100
[phone vibrating]

04:28.102 --> 04:31.570
Whoops, this isn't the kitchen.

04:31.572 --> 04:32.804
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:32.806 --> 04:34.239
- [groans]

04:34.241 --> 04:35.374
[whining]
- What?

04:35.376 --> 04:38.477
Now burger guy and smoothie guy
are hanging out

04:38.479 --> 04:40.479
without you?
- Leni?

04:40.481 --> 04:42.214
Are you in here again?

04:42.216 --> 04:44.216
My brother really needs to pee.

04:44.218 --> 04:46.518
- Sorry, I'll--
I'll be right out!

04:46.520 --> 04:47.586
Just washing my hands.

04:47.588 --> 04:50.222
I'm really sorry, guys,
I have to go.

04:50.224 --> 04:51.657
- Oh, I guess
your other friends

04:51.659 --> 04:53.458
are more important
than my life.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.227
- Fiona, it's not like that.

04:55.229 --> 04:56.728
- O-M-gosh, are you talking

04:56.730 --> 04:59.231
to your work friends right now?

04:59.233 --> 05:01.366
- [shrill scream]

05:01.368 --> 05:03.268
- Leni, are you okay?

05:03.270 --> 05:04.202
[faucet squeaks]

05:04.204 --> 05:05.504
- [yelps]
I'm so sorry!

05:05.506 --> 05:08.206
I--I'll clean it up.
- Don't bother.

05:08.208 --> 05:09.107
Mandee will help me.

05:09.109 --> 05:11.410
We won't take up
any more of your time.

05:11.412 --> 05:13.378
<i>- Yeah, neither will we.</i>

05:13.380 --> 05:15.447
<i>[dial tone]</i>

05:15.449 --> 05:18.417
<i>[downtrodden music]</i>

05:18.419 --> 05:19.251
[door opens]

05:19.253 --> 05:21.820
- [sighing repeatedly]

05:21.822 --> 05:23.455
- [scoffs]
Leni, your sighing

05:23.457 --> 05:25.190
is literally ruining
my texting.

05:25.192 --> 05:27.659
What's wrong?
- I don't know what to do.

05:27.661 --> 05:30.228
I feel torn between two groups
of friends.

05:30.230 --> 05:33.165
How do I make them both happy?
- [clears throat]

05:33.167 --> 05:34.800
- [scoffs]
Lincoln, what do you want?

05:34.802 --> 05:36.535
- I think I know how
to help Leni.

05:36.537 --> 05:39.137
When I started hanging out
with Rusty and Zach

05:39.139 --> 05:40.339
Clyde and Liam felt left out,

05:40.341 --> 05:43.175
so I invited everyone
to hang out together

05:43.177 --> 05:44.242
and now we're all BFFs.

05:44.244 --> 05:47.379
- So, you're saying my friends
should hang out

05:47.381 --> 05:49.614
with your friends?
- No.

05:49.616 --> 05:51.917
Bring your friends together.

05:51.919 --> 05:53.552
- Huh.
That is surprisingly

05:53.554 --> 05:55.520
mature advice
for an 11-year-old.

05:55.522 --> 05:57.155
- Thank you.
Now, if you'll excuse me,

05:57.157 --> 06:00.692
I have to go write my name
on my new Ace Savvy underwear.

06:00.694 --> 06:02.761
[underwear stretches, snaps]

06:02.763 --> 06:05.297
- I literally take that back.

06:05.299 --> 06:06.431
<i>[bouncy music]</i>

06:06.433 --> 06:08.834
<i>- We're gonna have</i>
<i>so much fun tonight.</i>

06:08.836 --> 06:11.570
I planned a bunch of stuff
for us to do.

06:11.572 --> 06:13.205
- Yogurt-covered pretzels?

06:13.207 --> 06:15.607
[gasps]
And "16 1/2 Magazine."

06:15.609 --> 06:19.177
My favorites.
- Ooh, sparkly water!

06:19.179 --> 06:21.580
Eww, who drinks
"pomelo" flavor?

06:21.582 --> 06:22.381
[doorbell rings]

06:22.383 --> 06:25.484
- Oh, good,
the other guests are here.

06:25.486 --> 06:26.918
And I got your favorite drink.:

06:26.920 --> 06:29.955
- Oh, I didn't realize
this was a "party" party.

06:29.957 --> 06:31.223
- It's just the five of us.

06:31.225 --> 06:33.759
I can't wait for you guys
to get to know each other.

06:33.761 --> 06:36.361
I thought we could play
a getting-to-know-you game.

06:36.363 --> 06:39.531
On each card is a fun fact
about someone in this room.

06:39.533 --> 06:40.766
Your job is to guess who.

06:40.768 --> 06:42.300
Miguel, you can go first.

06:42.302 --> 06:44.269
- "I like
pumpkin spice lattes."

06:44.271 --> 06:45.771
I'm gonna guess Mandee.
- [gasps]

06:45.773 --> 06:47.372
You're right.
How'd you know?

06:47.374 --> 06:49.775
- [disparaging laugh]
If your name's Mandee,

06:49.777 --> 06:52.544
liking pumpkin spice lattes
is pretty much

06:52.546 --> 06:53.578
your entire brand.

06:53.580 --> 06:56.982
- Wow, you guys know each other
so well already.

06:56.984 --> 06:58.483
Jackie, your turn.

06:58.485 --> 07:00.285
- "I have a winning smile."

07:00.287 --> 07:01.820
[giggles]
Well, that must be

07:01.822 --> 07:03.422
about Mandee.
- Actually,

07:03.424 --> 07:04.756
it was about Miguel.

07:04.758 --> 07:05.924
- Hmm, I don't see it.

07:05.926 --> 07:09.428
- I'm done with this game.
- Huh, which card says,

07:09.430 --> 07:10.395
"I'm a quitter"?

07:10.397 --> 07:13.698
- Uh, why don't we try
something else?

07:13.700 --> 07:16.668
Okay, I'll go first.

07:16.936 --> 07:17.936
Right foot apple.

07:17.938 --> 07:19.638
Mandee, why don't you go next?

07:19.640 --> 07:22.574
- Leni knows I'm good
at this game.

07:22.576 --> 07:24.843
Oh, left foot pineapple.

07:24.845 --> 07:25.877
- I'm pretty good at it, too.

07:25.879 --> 07:29.614
I'm a part-time
yoga instructor, so...

07:29.616 --> 07:30.715
Right foot grape.

07:30.717 --> 07:31.650
Leni, I didn't tell you.

07:31.652 --> 07:34.352
Yesterday, I had to deal with
a total Penny.

07:34.354 --> 07:36.521
- Oh, no, that's awful.

07:36.523 --> 07:37.823
A "Penny"
is what we call someone

07:37.825 --> 07:39.491
who tries using
an expired coupon.

07:39.493 --> 07:43.528
- You kind of have
to work with us to get it.

07:43.530 --> 07:44.729
- Leni, did you see

07:44.731 --> 07:46.698
Rashida's prom-posal
to Brandon?

07:46.700 --> 07:49.868
It was so addy-addy-bing-bang.

07:49.870 --> 07:51.770
- That's our friend word
for "adorable."

07:51.772 --> 07:54.439
- You kind of have
to go to school with us

07:54.441 --> 07:55.073
to get it.

07:55.075 --> 07:57.742
- Leni, I mean to thank you
for helping me get through

07:57.744 --> 07:59.277
that awful 12-hour sale.

07:59.279 --> 08:01.046
I was thinking about
how working together

08:01.048 --> 08:04.850
is pretty much
the deepest bond there is.

08:04.852 --> 08:05.550
- Really?

08:05.552 --> 08:07.452
'Cause I was thinking
that true friendship

08:07.454 --> 08:10.388
isn't something you can find
on a rack.

08:10.390 --> 08:12.591
<i>[combative music]</i>

08:12.593 --> 08:14.326
- [gasps]
My pomelo!

08:14.328 --> 08:16.061
- My bag!
- It was an accident.

08:16.063 --> 08:18.663
I'm sorry I'm not
a part-time yoga instructor.

08:18.665 --> 08:20.632
- Leni, this was
a terrible idea.

08:20.634 --> 08:21.933
Why did you want us
to hang out with them?

08:21.935 --> 08:24.769
- Well, believe me, we didn't
want to hang out with you.

08:24.771 --> 08:26.304
- [huffs]
We're leaving.

08:26.306 --> 08:27.973
- Don't bother, we're leaving.

08:27.975 --> 08:30.375
[all grunting]

08:30.377 --> 08:31.810
- Guys, wait!

08:31.812 --> 08:32.677
We didn't get to eat

08:32.679 --> 08:36.414
the "New Best Friends" cake
I baked.

08:36.416 --> 08:37.883
- Sorry, Leni.

08:37.885 --> 08:39.583
And by the way, Miguel,

08:39.586 --> 08:40.619
everyone likes pumpkin spice.

08:40.621 --> 08:43.722
Except maybe stuck-up
part-time yoga instructors.

08:43.724 --> 08:45.657
- [gasps]

08:45.659 --> 08:48.460
<i>[tense music]</i>

08:48.462 --> 08:49.160
- Wow, poor Leni.

08:49.162 --> 08:51.029
She's literally
bending over backwards

08:51.031 --> 08:52.998
for her friends.
- [groans]

08:53.000 --> 08:54.633
[yelps]

08:54.635 --> 08:56.568
- [groans]
These clothes will go out

08:56.570 --> 08:59.371
of style before I get
to try them on.

08:59.373 --> 09:00.505
- Oh, it's you.

09:00.507 --> 09:02.007
Ugh.
- Didn't Leni tell you

09:02.009 --> 09:03.775
that fuchsia
was last season's color?

09:03.777 --> 09:05.410
- Mm, guess she didn't tell you

09:05.412 --> 09:06.845
that you can't pull off
those jeans.

09:06.847 --> 09:08.980
- [horrified gasp]
- That's it.

09:08.982 --> 09:11.516
Leni, come out.
You have to choose.

09:11.518 --> 09:13.084
Either them or us.

09:13.086 --> 09:14.986
Oops.
[awkward laugh]

09:14.988 --> 09:15.654
My bad.

09:15.656 --> 09:17.489
Wait, isn't Leni
with you guys?

09:17.491 --> 09:18.757
- We thought she was with you.

09:18.759 --> 09:21.593
[gasps]
Is she blowing us all off?

09:21.595 --> 09:24.396
<i>- On this week's episode</i>
<i>of "Best Friends Forever,"</i>

09:24.398 --> 09:26.498
<i>Kurt is torn</i>
<i>between suede fringe</i>

09:26.500 --> 09:29.100
<i>and classic pinstripe.</i>
<i>- Luckily, my best friends</i>

09:29.102 --> 09:32.637
<i>are here to help me choose</i>
<i>the perfect vest.</i>

09:32.639 --> 09:33.772
- [weeping]

09:33.774 --> 09:34.673
[phone ringing]

09:34.675 --> 09:36.741
Hello?
- Leni, what the heck?

09:36.743 --> 09:38.543
Where are you?
- Oh, hey.

09:38.545 --> 09:41.379
How's the pop-up sale?
- Never mind that.

09:41.381 --> 09:42.047
You ditched us.

09:42.049 --> 09:44.616
Do you have another group
of friends we don't know about?

09:44.618 --> 09:45.216
- I'm sorry.

09:45.218 --> 09:47.052
I knew that no matter
who I went to the sale with

09:47.054 --> 09:50.956
I'd be upsetting someone,
so I decided to stay home.

09:50.958 --> 09:52.090
I'll let you guys go.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.826
I don't want to ruin your day.

09:54.828 --> 09:55.527
- Wow.

09:55.529 --> 09:59.030
Leni missed her favorite sale
because of us.

09:59.032 --> 09:59.898
- Ugh.

09:59.900 --> 10:01.933
We are the worst.

10:01.935 --> 10:05.704
- Leni, we need to talk to you.
- We overheard your phone call

10:05.706 --> 10:06.771
and we're worried about you.

10:06.773 --> 10:08.740
It's not your fault
if your friends

10:08.742 --> 10:10.141
can't get along.
- It's not?

10:10.143 --> 10:12.577
- No, and if they can't
hang out together,

10:12.579 --> 10:14.779
they'll just have to learn
to share you.

10:14.781 --> 10:16.748
- You know what? You're right.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.184
- Now you march over
to the store and tell hem

10:19.186 --> 10:21.620
that they're gonna have
to grow up.

10:21.622 --> 10:23.888
- Yeah, I will do that!

10:23.890 --> 10:26.958
<i>[rousing music]</i>

10:26.960 --> 10:28.727
Oh, you're here.
Well, good.

10:28.729 --> 10:30.095
There's something I have
to say to you.

10:30.097 --> 10:33.198
- Actually, there's something
we have to say to you.

10:33.200 --> 10:34.065
- No, me first.

10:34.067 --> 10:36.801
If you can't share the store,
then you're going to have

10:36.803 --> 10:39.738
to march over to the room
and grow me up.

10:39.740 --> 10:40.972
Wait, that's not right.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.908
Dang it, I was gonna
practice this on the bus.

10:43.910 --> 10:45.477
- Leni, never mind that.

10:45.479 --> 10:46.845
We came to apologize.

10:46.847 --> 10:48.780
- We've been acting
like total jerks.

10:48.782 --> 10:49.981
I'm sorry we got so jealous.

10:49.983 --> 10:52.450
- Even if the four of us
aren't gonna be besties,

10:52.452 --> 10:53.885
we can at least try
to get along.

10:53.887 --> 10:56.855
- 'Cause the last thing
any of us want is to lose you

10:56.857 --> 10:58.857
as a friend.
- Aww.

10:58.859 --> 11:00.525
That's supes sweet.

11:00.527 --> 11:01.226
Thanks, you guys.

11:01.228 --> 11:02.727
Hey, do you want to come in?

11:02.729 --> 11:05.497
I was just watching
"Best Friends Forever."

11:05.499 --> 11:07.932
both: I love that show!

11:07.934 --> 11:09.167
<i>- [laughing]</i>
<i>R--right?</i>

11:09.169 --> 11:10.769
<i>I mean, how could you</i>
<i>go wrong?</i>

11:10.771 --> 11:14.139
- That vest is so
addy-addy-bing-bang

11:14.141 --> 11:17.742
- Hey, this pomelo's
really tasty.

11:17.744 --> 11:19.177
Good call, Miguel.

11:19.179 --> 11:22.480
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

11:23.949 --> 11:27.118
<i>[radical rock music]</i>

11:27.120 --> 11:32.791
<i>♪</i>

11:32.793 --> 11:34.092
- [yells]

11:34.094 --> 11:37.529
[sniffs]
Do I smell cookies?

11:37.531 --> 11:39.731
- Yeah, but don't waste
your time.

11:39.733 --> 11:42.467
They're "not for family."

11:42.469 --> 11:44.769
<i>[lighthearted music]</i>

11:44.771 --> 11:48.073
- Hey, Stinkin', think fast.

11:48.075 --> 11:49.474
[munching]
- Lynn!

11:49.476 --> 11:51.576
- It's okay, we needed
a taste-tester.

11:51.578 --> 11:53.978
I'm worried the bottoms
are soggy.

11:53.980 --> 11:55.847
- Nope, nice crunch.

11:55.849 --> 11:58.149
What are they for?
- Clyde and I have

11:58.151 --> 11:59.951
middle-school orientation
tomorrow.

11:59.953 --> 12:02.487
- [splutters]
You guys are coming

12:02.489 --> 12:04.055
to my school?
- Yeah!

12:04.057 --> 12:05.690
We got assigned
an 8th grade buddy

12:05.692 --> 12:07.058
who's gonna take us around
and show us

12:07.060 --> 12:09.027
what the next three years
of our lives will be like.

12:09.029 --> 12:11.429
- And we want to make
a good impression,

12:11.431 --> 12:13.431
so we're coming prepared.

12:13.433 --> 12:15.734
Designed these ourselves.

12:15.736 --> 12:18.903
- "Clincoln McCloud- BFFs."

12:18.905 --> 12:19.971
Cookies and business cards?

12:19.973 --> 12:21.706
That's your plan?
- I'm also planning

12:21.708 --> 12:24.909
to use word association
to learn everyone's names.

12:24.911 --> 12:27.512
Like, "Lynn once bruised

12:27.514 --> 12:28.113
my shin."

12:28.115 --> 12:30.048
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait, time out.

12:30.050 --> 12:32.917
This stuff might fly
in elementary school, okay?

12:32.919 --> 12:34.886
But middle school is different.

12:34.888 --> 12:35.687
It's the jungle.

12:35.689 --> 12:37.122
If you walk in there
looking like a couple

12:37.124 --> 12:40.458
of weak chumps,
you'll get eaten alive.

12:40.460 --> 12:41.226
<i>[jaguar growls]</i>

12:41.228 --> 12:42.127
both: Eaten alive?

12:42.129 --> 12:43.561
- Does that mean
we should reconsider

12:43.563 --> 12:46.765
wearing matching turtlenecks?
- Ugh.

12:46.767 --> 12:48.666
- Don't worry,
LJ's got your back.

12:48.668 --> 12:51.569
<i>- [garbled voice]</i>
<i>- Yo, Principal Ramirez.</i>

12:51.571 --> 12:53.605
Lynn Loud.
Hey, listen, who can I talk to

12:53.607 --> 12:56.074
about becoming
an orientation buddy?

12:56.076 --> 12:58.143
- Psst, don't throw out
those business cards.

12:58.145 --> 13:00.078
They might still work
for high school.

13:00.080 --> 13:02.680
<i>[dramatic musical flourish]</i>

13:02.682 --> 13:03.681
<i>[peppy music]</i>

13:03.683 --> 13:05.850
<i>[indistinct chatter]</i>
<i>Lincoln!</i>

13:05.852 --> 13:07.218
Check out those columns!

13:07.220 --> 13:09.187
Do you think they're
real marble?

13:09.189 --> 13:09.988
- Probably.

13:09.990 --> 13:12.023
This place is so much bigger
than our school.

13:12.025 --> 13:14.058
Good thing they gave us maps.

13:14.060 --> 13:15.093
- Huh?

13:15.095 --> 13:17.495
Guys, guys, guys,
ditch the maps.

13:17.497 --> 13:19.030
First rule of survival:

13:19.032 --> 13:21.032
Don't act like a total noob.

13:21.034 --> 13:22.267
- But we are noobs.

13:22.269 --> 13:25.170
- Yeah, and if some
upperclassman realizes that,

13:25.172 --> 13:27.238
you'll be a prime target
for pranks.

13:27.240 --> 13:30.275
Like the kid who asked
an eighth grader for directions

13:30.277 --> 13:32.544
on the first day of school.

13:32.546 --> 13:35.713
<i>The poor fool got sent</i>
<i>on a wild-goose-chase</i>

13:35.715 --> 13:37.115
<i>down in the tunnels</i>
<i>under the school</i>

13:37.117 --> 13:40.251
<i>and didn't make it out</i>
<i>until the whole day was over.</i>

13:40.253 --> 13:42.153
<i>[ominous music]</i>

13:42.155 --> 13:43.121
[both gasp]

13:43.123 --> 13:46.090
both: Don't... be... noobs.

13:46.092 --> 13:48.259
[bell rings]

13:48.261 --> 13:49.127
- Okay, homeroom.

13:49.129 --> 13:51.296
There are no assigned seats,
so it's time

13:51.298 --> 13:54.632
for rule number two:
Don't get stuck with

13:54.634 --> 13:56.234
a crummy desk.

13:56.236 --> 13:58.269
Move out!

13:58.271 --> 13:59.537
- Oh, sorry.

13:59.539 --> 14:00.338
Please, it's all yours.

14:00.340 --> 14:02.273
I'd pull out the chair
for you, but...

14:02.275 --> 14:05.677
[clears throat]
It's attached.

14:05.679 --> 14:07.145
- Wrong.

14:07.147 --> 14:08.780
Hey, back off, pigtails.

14:08.782 --> 14:11.282
My buddy saw this first.

14:11.284 --> 14:13.284
[grunts]
Boom, dominant.

14:13.286 --> 14:15.153
Nobody's messing with that.

14:15.155 --> 14:17.055
Hah.
- Uh, wasn't that

14:17.057 --> 14:18.890
a little aggressive?
- [grunts]

14:18.892 --> 14:20.558
Not if you don't want
to end up like the kid

14:20.560 --> 14:23.728
who got stuck with
the worst desk in the room.

14:23.730 --> 14:25.096
<i>[ominous music]</i>

14:25.098 --> 14:25.897
[cruel laughter]

14:25.899 --> 14:28.132
<i>This one kid thought she had</i>
<i>the perfect desk,</i>

14:28.134 --> 14:30.301
<i>but ended up getting stuck</i>
<i>in it so tight</i>

14:30.303 --> 14:33.271
<i>that they had to call</i>
<i>the school cook.</i>

14:33.273 --> 14:34.105
- Sorry, kid.

14:34.107 --> 14:36.875
We're gonna have to
grease you out.

14:36.877 --> 14:39.244
You got any nut allergies?

14:39.246 --> 14:41.346
[menacing laughter]

14:41.348 --> 14:45.817
both: Don't get stuck
with crummy desks.

14:45.819 --> 14:47.919
- Okay, next is Bio.

14:47.921 --> 14:49.320
Suit up.
- Cool!

14:49.322 --> 14:51.723
I've always wanted to wear
a lab coat.

14:51.725 --> 14:52.690
- Welcome, fifth graders.

14:52.692 --> 14:54.826
We are continuing our work
with live mealworms today,

14:54.828 --> 14:58.930
so everyone grab a case
from the back of the class.

15:00.032 --> 15:01.366
- [grunts]

15:01.368 --> 15:03.935
[all screaming]

15:03.937 --> 15:05.169
- Sorry, guys!

15:05.171 --> 15:06.070
That was my fault.

15:06.072 --> 15:08.373
I was up late making...
- [hollering]

15:08.375 --> 15:09.841
- Lynn, what the heck?

15:09.843 --> 15:11.309
- Rule number three:
Never own up

15:11.311 --> 15:14.312
to making a mistake.
- But I spilled the worms.

15:14.314 --> 15:15.713
- So?
Do you want to be like

15:15.715 --> 15:18.783
the sixth grader who--hang on,
Clyde needs to hear this, too.

15:18.785 --> 15:19.617
- [whimpering]

15:19.619 --> 15:21.986
- Do you want to be like
the sixth-grader who owned up

15:21.988 --> 15:24.822
to farting during
a standardized test?

15:24.824 --> 15:25.723
<i>[ominous music]</i>

15:25.725 --> 15:29.193
- Hey, look,
it's Farty McStink Pants!

15:29.195 --> 15:33.197
both: Own up to nothing.

15:33.899 --> 15:35.133
- [growling]
- [laughs]

15:35.135 --> 15:37.835
Loving the agro body language.

15:37.837 --> 15:38.436
Here you go.

15:38.438 --> 15:42.006
Double-meatball subs
with extra sriracha.

15:42.008 --> 15:42.707
- Thanks.

15:42.709 --> 15:43.841
I'm normally not
a hot sauce guy,

15:43.843 --> 15:47.645
but after this morning
I'm feeling dangerous.

15:47.647 --> 15:48.680
[munching]

15:48.682 --> 15:50.381
- Great, so my rules
are sinking in?

15:50.383 --> 15:52.083
- Yeah, some kid just came over

15:52.085 --> 15:53.985
to ask if she could borrow
a chair,

15:53.987 --> 15:55.320
and guess what Clyde said?

15:55.322 --> 15:57.956
- [deep voice]
I don't think so, pal.

15:57.958 --> 15:58.790
- Boom.

15:58.792 --> 15:59.924
McBride for the win.

15:59.926 --> 16:01.292
- So what are we doing
after lunch?

16:01.294 --> 16:03.294
- Well, actually,
we orientation buddies

16:03.296 --> 16:06.331
are supposed to let you guys
fly solo for the rest

16:06.333 --> 16:07.131
of the day.

16:07.133 --> 16:08.833
See how you do on your own.
- Really?

16:08.835 --> 16:10.134
- Already?
- Don't worry.

16:10.136 --> 16:12.003
You guys totally got this.

16:12.005 --> 16:13.338
Now, hands in.

16:13.340 --> 16:14.439
Three, two, one...

16:14.441 --> 16:16.774
all: Dominate!
- Wow, Clyde,

16:16.776 --> 16:18.009
your hands are so soft.

16:18.011 --> 16:22.013
- Oh, thank you.
- We'll work on that.

16:22.015 --> 16:24.015
- First class of the afternoon:

16:24.017 --> 16:26.150
"The Wonders of Watercolors."

16:26.152 --> 16:28.753
- To the Art department!

16:28.755 --> 16:31.756
Uh, which way is that again?

16:31.758 --> 16:34.158
- Maybe if we just take
a quick peek at the map...

16:34.160 --> 16:36.160
- No!
Lynn's first rule, remember?

16:36.162 --> 16:39.230
Don't look like a noob.
- Right.

16:39.232 --> 16:41.199
[bell ringing]

16:41.201 --> 16:42.400
- [both gasp]

16:42.402 --> 16:43.701
[doors slamming]

16:43.703 --> 16:46.070
- Oh, no,
we're gonna be tardy!

16:46.072 --> 16:48.139
- Hey, you guys lost?

16:48.141 --> 16:49.340
- Nice try, bucko!

16:49.342 --> 16:51.809
But we're not falling
for one of your

16:51.811 --> 16:54.178
upper classmen pranks.

16:54.180 --> 16:56.748
[hyperventilating]
- Way to dominate, Clyde.

16:56.750 --> 16:58.282
"Bucko" was a nice touch.
- Thanks.

16:58.284 --> 17:01.252
My dads were watching
a cop show last night.

17:01.254 --> 17:02.286
<i>[ambient music]</i>

17:02.288 --> 17:04.122
- This looks like
the Art department.

17:04.124 --> 17:07.025
Maybe this is
the watercolor room.

17:07.027 --> 17:08.159
[kids hollering]

17:08.161 --> 17:09.426
- Are you kidding me?
- Go away!

17:09.429 --> 17:11.896
- Is this "The Wonders
of Watercolors"?

17:11.897 --> 17:14.165
- No, this is
"Fun With Photography,"

17:14.166 --> 17:16.401
and you just ruined
a whole months' work.

17:16.403 --> 17:18.202
I'll see you jerks
after school.

17:18.204 --> 17:20.271
Meet me on the blacktop
at 3:00.

17:20.272 --> 17:23.875
- You think she's inviting us
to play a game of tetherball?

17:23.877 --> 17:27.178
- No, that's where we fight.

17:27.180 --> 17:28.279
[both swallow]

17:28.281 --> 17:30.748
- Okay, so we ticked off
one photo student,

17:30.750 --> 17:32.917
but I'm sure we can
smooth everything over

17:32.919 --> 17:34.252
after school.
- I'm already writing

17:34.254 --> 17:37.355
the apology letter in my head.
- Come on, let's grab a seat

17:37.357 --> 17:38.322
Remember rule number two!

17:38.324 --> 17:40.992
These look nice and sturdy.
- Plus, we can make

17:40.994 --> 17:44.228
great eye contact
with the teacher from here.

17:44.230 --> 17:45.296
- Oh.
Hey, dudes.

17:45.298 --> 17:47.198
Those are actually our seats.

17:47.200 --> 17:51.169
- [clears throat]
We saw them first, bud.

17:51.171 --> 17:52.236
- Um, okay.

17:52.238 --> 17:53.838
Well, seats are assigned,

17:53.840 --> 17:56.140
and those are
legitimately ours.

17:56.142 --> 17:58.810
- Pssh, a likely story.

17:58.812 --> 17:59.510
[bell ringing]

17:59.512 --> 18:01.112
- Come on, man!
- Byron, Cici,

18:01.114 --> 18:02.313
what are you doing
out of your seats?

18:02.315 --> 18:05.283
I expect every student
to be ready to work

18:05.285 --> 18:06.284
when the bell rings.

18:06.286 --> 18:08.119
You two just earned zeroes

18:08.121 --> 18:10.121
for participation.
[both gasp]

18:10.123 --> 18:13.157
- Meet us on the blacktop
at 3:00.

18:13.159 --> 18:15.893
<i>♪</i>

18:15.895 --> 18:17.929
- How come we have
so many enemies?

18:17.931 --> 18:20.465
We don't even go here yet.
- Relax.

18:20.467 --> 18:21.999
This is our last class
of the day.

18:22.001 --> 18:24.235
Let's just keep a low profile
and try not to make

18:24.237 --> 18:26.104
anyone else hate us.
- Got it.

18:26.106 --> 18:28.239
- Okay, people,
I spent all morning

18:28.241 --> 18:31.109
buffing the dumb floor
for the PTA banquet

18:31.111 --> 18:32.477
so no dodgeball today.

18:32.479 --> 18:34.846
You're watching
a movie instead.

18:34.848 --> 18:36.814
[all cheering]

18:36.816 --> 18:37.448
- Perfect.

18:37.450 --> 18:40.084
There's no way
we can mess this up.

18:40.086 --> 18:41.119
[shoes squeaking]

18:41.121 --> 18:42.220
[both shout, grunt]

18:42.222 --> 18:44.422
- [gasps]
- [screams]

18:44.424 --> 18:45.456
[metal clattering]

18:45.458 --> 18:48.259
- Who's responsible for this?

18:48.261 --> 18:50.194
- Remember rule number three:

18:50.196 --> 18:52.029
never own up
to making a mistake.

18:52.031 --> 18:55.066
- Well, since no one's fessin'
to the messin',

18:55.068 --> 18:56.868
you can forget that movie.

18:56.870 --> 18:58.603
You're all cleaning up instead.

18:58.605 --> 18:59.537
[crash]

18:59.539 --> 19:00.404
[all groan]

19:00.406 --> 19:03.141
- [angry muttering]
- Don't feel bad, buddy.

19:03.143 --> 19:05.610
If we admitted it was us,
we'd be the next

19:05.612 --> 19:06.944
Farty McStink Pants.

19:06.946 --> 19:09.313
- It was you?
You're making us clean?

19:09.315 --> 19:11.015
- [angry exclamation]
- You meet us

19:11.017 --> 19:13.851
on the blacktop at...
- Yeah, yeah, we know.

19:13.853 --> 19:16.020
On the blacktop, 3:00.

19:16.022 --> 19:17.522
<i>♪</i>

19:17.524 --> 19:19.323
[bell ringing]

19:19.325 --> 19:21.359
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:21.361 --> 19:23.194
[birds cawing]

19:23.196 --> 19:25.062
- Uh-oh.

19:25.064 --> 19:27.632
<i>♪</i>

19:27.634 --> 19:28.633
Guys, what's going on?

19:28.635 --> 19:31.636
- Well, it's a long story,
but I'm pretty sure it ends

19:31.638 --> 19:35.339
with those kids
kicking our butts.

19:35.607 --> 19:36.607
- [munching]

19:36.609 --> 19:39.577
- What the heck happened?
- We tried following your rules

19:39.579 --> 19:41.612
but people didn't think
we're tough.

19:41.614 --> 19:43.281
- They just think we're jerks,

19:43.283 --> 19:45.049
and I'm not sure I disagree.

19:45.051 --> 19:47.985
- Yeah, so thanks
for the great advice.

19:47.987 --> 19:48.953
- I'm sorry.

19:48.955 --> 19:50.888
I was just trying
to spare you guys

19:50.890 --> 19:52.990
from what happened to me.

19:52.992 --> 19:54.625
both: Huh?
- Yeah, my first year

19:54.627 --> 19:58.229
of middle school
was a real horror story.

19:58.231 --> 19:59.664
<i>♪</i>

19:59.666 --> 20:02.366
Um, excuse me,
could you tell me

20:02.368 --> 20:04.502
how to get to the gym?

20:04.504 --> 20:06.070
- Oh, sure, it's really easy.

20:06.072 --> 20:08.506
Just head down
those stairs over there.

20:08.508 --> 20:10.141
[both laughing]

20:10.143 --> 20:12.276
- So that story you told us

20:12.278 --> 20:15.146
was about you?
- Yep.

20:15.148 --> 20:18.082
[sighs]
They were all me.

20:18.084 --> 20:19.650
[children laughing]

20:19.652 --> 20:22.353
all chanting:
Farty pants! Farty pants!

20:22.355 --> 20:25.556
- I finally figured out
that if I acted tough,

20:25.558 --> 20:27.091
people would stop
messing with me,

20:27.093 --> 20:29.994
and since it worked for me
I thought it could help

20:29.996 --> 20:31.696
protect you guys, too.

20:31.698 --> 20:34.232
- Wow, I had no idea
you went through all that.

20:34.234 --> 20:36.200
- Me neither,
and it was nice of you

20:36.202 --> 20:39.070
to try and help us,
even though it's gonna lead

20:39.072 --> 20:40.037
to a lot of pain.

20:40.039 --> 20:41.372
[whimpers]
- No, it's not,

20:41.374 --> 20:44.208
because I'm gonna take
the heat for you guys.

20:44.210 --> 20:46.377
both: No, no, no!
- We have to go.

20:46.379 --> 20:48.546
- Some of those kids
might still be here next year.

20:48.548 --> 20:51.015
They're gonna think we're wimps
who let other people

20:51.017 --> 20:53.084
fight our battles.
- Though, when you think

20:53.086 --> 20:57.021
about it, would that really
be so bad?

20:57.023 --> 20:58.422
Okay, okay.

20:58.424 --> 21:01.726
<i>[suspenseful Western music]</i>

21:01.728 --> 21:07.965
<i>♪</i>

21:07.967 --> 21:10.067
[watch beeps]

21:10.069 --> 21:11.669
[both shouting]

21:11.671 --> 21:14.572
[both grunting]

21:15.040 --> 21:16.107
- Ugh.

21:16.109 --> 21:18.576
- [laughs weakly]
I guess you guys don't have

21:18.578 --> 21:20.344
to beat us up
because apparently

21:20.346 --> 21:22.546
we can do it ourselves.

21:22.548 --> 21:23.648
[all laughing]

21:23.650 --> 21:26.050
- Aww, we weren't really gonna
beat you up.

21:26.052 --> 21:28.619
We just wanted
to make you sweat a little.

21:28.621 --> 21:29.587
- Well, it worked.

21:29.589 --> 21:32.189
This is my third shirt
of the day.

21:32.191 --> 21:33.724
[all laughing]

21:33.726 --> 21:35.559
- Here, kid,
you dropped your--

21:35.561 --> 21:38.129
hey, are these snickerdoodles?

21:38.131 --> 21:40.398
- Uh, yeah.
Homemade.

21:40.400 --> 21:43.067
Help yourself.
[all munching]

21:43.069 --> 21:44.068
- Wow, these are good.

21:44.070 --> 21:46.504
What's your name, again?
- I'm Clyde McBride,

21:46.506 --> 21:47.738
and this is Lincoln Loud.

21:47.740 --> 21:50.775
We're also known as
Clincoln McCloud.

21:50.777 --> 21:53.678
"Clincoln McCloud, BFFs."

21:53.680 --> 21:56.113
